chapters.title: There were SEVEN FEAST days of our Lord. (Passover, Unleavened, First-fruits, Pentecost, Atonement, Trumpets and Tabernacle). (Leviticus 23:1-44)
Job had SEVEN sons. When his friends came to visit him they sat SEVEN days and SEVEN nights in silence, and afterward they were required to offer a Burnt Offering of SEVEN bullocks and SEVEN rams

Nebuchadnezzar made an image of gold to be worshipped. At that time he called together SEVEN kinds of officials to the dedication of the image: (1) princes, (2) governors, (3) captains, (4) judges, (5) treasurers (6) counselors, (7) sheriffs.
Seven times seventy were extended for forgiveness. 15.Seven devils cast out of Mary Magdalene. 16 Seven deacons chosen to help the work of the church.
Seven Golden Candlesticks 19.Seven stars in God's right hand. 20. Seven Angels.
What will not be mingled with the falling of the seven last plagues? Habakkuk3:2 Revelation 14:9,10
What will be the duration of the seven last plagues? Revelation

What takes place under the second plague? [Rev 16:3]
What takes place under the third plague? [Rev 16:4-7]
